				<li id="16750011" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1659585761000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580158/Inseparable-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 Aug 2022 00:02</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16750011" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This has probably been the best holy sword I&apos;ve used. I created a new Faith character and used this most of the time since getting strong enough to defeat the dragon to acquire it. I have to say I&apos;m scratching my head why it would be worth bothering with the Golden Order Greatsword given it seems the Inseparable Sword continues to do more damage as they scale up. The only mild weakness I&apos;ve find with the Inseparable Sword is that it has a common weapon art, which I&apos;d note isn&apos;t even a bad one, just not a sexy and unique one. The fact that Sacred Blade also buffs your weapon damage briefly on top of already having a very high AR is very useful. I underestimated how handy not needing to double tap undead enemies can be. When you have about 5 strong undead enemies in Farum Azula trying to maul you, it becomes much easier to appreciate that benefit of them not coming back to life without the additional final hit.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16750011" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-